   Category: Self-Employment

   Business ownership has long been a tool by which millions of Americans
   enter the social and economic mainstream, and the current social and
   economic climate presents unprecedented opportunities for aspiring
   entrepreneurs with disabilities. Look here to find everything you need
   to know about starting a small business, including information on how
   to write a business plan and resources on financing and training.

